==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dioptre
<hw>Di*op"tre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See 2d
<er>Dioptric</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>A unit employed by
oculists in numbering glasses according to the metric system; a
refractive power equal to that of a glass whose principal focal distance
is one meter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dioptric</ent>⟦br⟧
